headline: MoneyMasters Podcast 9-18-25- What's Really Powering the Rally in Stocks and Metals
summary: In this episode of the MoneyShow MoneyMasters Podcast, Sean Brodrick of Weiss Ratings and John Eade of Argus Research unpack today’s market drivers, record equities, gold’s strongest year since 1979, and ongoing Federal Reserve interest rate cuts.

headline: From scrappy challenger to IPO: Chris Britt brings Chime’s playbook to TechCrunch Disrupt 2025
summary: Chris Britt brings Chime’s playbook to TechCrunch Disrupt 2025 in October. Whether you’re building in fintech or another fast-moving sector, this is a rare opportunity to hear firsthand how to scale with resilience, discipline, and purpose. Register now before Regular Bird rates go up in a week.

headline: Is Now the Right Time to Consider Visa After Strong Year-to-Date Gains?
summary: If you have ever wondered whether Visa is a buy, hold, or sell right now, you are definitely not alone. Investors often find themselves at this crossroads, especially as the stock continues to ride upward trends and navigate shifting market currents. Visa’s performance has been impressive, to say the least. Over the last week, the stock gained 2.4%, with a 1.0% rise in the past month. Step back a little further, and you will see a year-to-date gain of 10.1% and an astonishing 20.9% return...
